properties.Title: Extreme Cold Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Dangerous wind chill values in the -45 to -55 range have spread across areas of northern Manitoba. These wind chill values will moderate for most regions later today but areas in extreme northern Manitoba could see a return tonight into Thursday morning. ### Extreme cold puts everyone at risk. Watch for cold related symptoms: shortness of breath, chest pain, muscle pain and weakness, numbness and colour change in fingers and toes. Extreme cold warnings are issued when very cold temperatures or wind chill creates an elevated risk to health such as frost bite and hypothermia. For more information on cold and your health, visit Manitoba Health at https://www.gov.mb.ca/health/publichealth/environmentalhealth/cold.html or call Health Links - Info Sant√© at 204-788-8200 or toll-free at 1-888-315-9257. properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Bad weather expected this evening. Intense flurries and strong winds are expected this evening, giving momentarily near zero visibilities in snow and blowing snow. Then, a significant drop in temperatures is expected, which could make some roads icy and slippery. The intense cold will then settle, and wind chill values could reach between minus 45 and minus 50 Friday morning. Driving conditions may be hazardous at times. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to QCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #QCStorm.
